Write a program to find the longest contiguous subarray of integers where the sum of even numbers equals the sum of odd numbers.

Requirements

Read an integer N (array size) and then N integers.

Find the length of the longest contiguous subarray where:

sum(even numbers)
=
sum(odd numbers)
sum(even numbers)=sum(odd numbers)

Output the length and the subarray itself (first occurrence if multiple).

If no such subarray exists, output 0 or mention.
